            <p class="card-text">
              Sheila is a postdoctoral researcher in the Biological and Agricultural
              Engineering Department at NC State. She received her BS degree in Biological
              Engineering from Binghamton University and MS and PhD degrees in Biological and
              Environmental Engineering from Cornell University. Clams are her favorite
              shellfish, especially in chowder or on top of linguini.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
